from itertools import permutations
for j in range(int(input())):
 n=input()
 c=""
 x=list(permutations(n,2))
 a=set(x)
 for i in a:
  z=i[0]+i[1]
  if(int(z)>=65 and int(z)<=90):
   c+=chr(int(z))
 if(c==""):
  print("")
 else:
  am=list(c)
  am.sort()
  bm="".join(am)
  print(bm)
